#: ../../source/install/config-mattermost-server.rst:2
msgid "Configuring Mattermost Server"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-mattermost-server.rst:4
msgid "Create the System Admin user and set up Mattermost for general use."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-mattermost-server.rst:6
msgid ""
"Open a browser and navigate to your Mattermost instance. For example, if "
"the IP address of the Mattermost server is ``10.10.10.2`` then go to "
"http://10.10.10.2:8065."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-mattermost-server.rst:8
msgid ""
"Create the first team and user. The first user in the system has the "
"``system_admin`` role, which gives you access to the System Console."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-mattermost-server.rst:10
msgid ""
"Open the System Console. To open the System Console, click your username "
"at the top of the navigation panel, and in the menu that opens, click "
"**System Console**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-mattermost-server.rst:12
msgid "Set the Site URL:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-mattermost-server.rst:13
msgid ""
"In the GENERAL section of the System Console, click **Configuration** in "
"prior versions or **System Console** > **Environment** > **Web Server** "
"in versions after 5.12."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-mattermost-server.rst:14
msgid ""
"In the **Site URL** field, set the URL that users point their browsers "
"at. For example, *https://mattermost.example.com*. If you are using "
"HTTPS, make sure that you set up TLS, either on Mattermost Server or on a"
" proxy."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-mattermost-server.rst:16
msgid "Set up email notifications."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-mattermost-server.rst:18
msgid ""
"In the NOTIFICATIONS section of the System Console, make the following "
"changes:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-mattermost-server.rst:20
msgid "Set **Enable Email Notifications** to *true*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-mattermost-server.rst:21
msgid "Set **Notification Display Name** to *No-Reply*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-mattermost-server.rst:22
msgid ""
"Set **Notification From Address** to *{your-domain-name}* For example, "
"*example.com*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-mattermost-server.rst:24
msgid ""
"In the NOTIFICATIONS section of the System Console in prior versions or "
"**System Console** > **Environment** > **SMTP** in versions after 5.12, "
"also make the following changes:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-mattermost-server.rst:26
msgid ""
"Set **SMTP Server Username** to *{SMTP-username}* For example, "
"*admin@example.com*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-mattermost-server.rst:27
msgid "Set **SMTP Server Password** to *{SMTP-password}*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-mattermost-server.rst:28
msgid "Set **SMTP Server** to *{SMTP-server}* For example, *mail.example.com*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-mattermost-server.rst:29
msgid "Set **SMTP Server Port** to *465*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-mattermost-server.rst:30
msgid ""
"Set **Connection Security** to *TLS* or *STARTTLS*, depending on what the"
" SMTP server accepts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-mattermost-server.rst:32
msgid "Click **Test Connection**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-mattermost-server.rst:34
msgid "After your connection is working, click **Save**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-mattermost-server.rst:36
msgid "Set up the file and image storage location."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-mattermost-server.rst:39
msgid ""
"Files and images that users attach to their messages are not stored in "
"the database. Instead, they are stored in a location that you specify. "
"You can store the files on the local file system or in Amazon S3."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-mattermost-server.rst:40
msgid ""
"Make sure that the location has enough free space. The amount of storage "
"that's required depends on the number of users and on the number and size"
" of files that users attach to messages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-mattermost-server.rst:42
msgid ""
"In the FILES section of the System Console, click **Storage** in prior "
"versions or **System Console** > **Environment** > **File Storage** in "
"versions after 5.12."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-mattermost-server.rst:43
msgid ""
"If you store the files locally, set **File Storage System** to *Local "
"File System*, and then either accept the default for the **Local Storage "
"Directory** or enter a location. The location must be a directory that "
"exists and has write permissions for the Mattermost server. It can be an "
"absolute path or a relative path. Relative paths are relative to the "
"``mattermost`` directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-mattermost-server.rst:44
msgid ""
"If you store the files on Amazon S3, set **File Storage System** to "
"*Amazon S3* and enter the appropriate values for your Amazon account."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-mattermost-server.rst:45
msgid "Click **Save**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-mattermost-server.rst:47
msgid ""
"Review the other settings in the System Console to make sure everything "
"is as you want it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-mattermost-server.rst:49
msgid "Restart the Mattermost Service."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-mattermost-server.rst:51
msgid "On Ubuntu 14.04 and RHEL 6:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-mattermost-server.rst:53
msgid "``sudo restart mattermost``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-mattermost-server.rst:55
msgid "On Ubuntu 16.04, 18.04, Debian Stretch, and RHEL 7:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-mattermost-server.rst:57
msgid "``sudo systemctl restart mattermost``"
msgstr ""

